\title{bayesianICSimulations: Bayesian Interval-Censored Survival Data Simulation and Analysis}
\description{
Tools for simulating interval-censored survival data and comparing Bayesian inference methods (HMC via Stan, Metropolis-Hastings via JAGS) for log-logistic AFT models. Designed for MSc research on MCMC comparison with weighted interval-censored data. Includes visualization tools for exploratory analysis and standardized analysis pipelines following the ADEMP framework.

Tools for comparing Bayesian MCMC methods (HMC via Stan, Metropolis-Hastings
via JAGS) for fitting log-logistic AFT models to interval-censored survival
data with survey weights. Designed for MSc research following the ADEMP
simulation framework.

Functions to visualize parametric log-logistic survival
estimates from interval-censored data with survey weights, comparing
fitted curves across simulation replicates to true population curves.
}
